commit.message:
vkd3d: Do not use 2D_ARRAY_COMPATIBLE + SPARSE + 3D.

Does not work on Intel and Vulkan bans it.

Signed-off-by: Hans-Kristian Arntzen <post@arntzen-software.no>

tests: Fix DXIL ATOC test on Windows.

Derp, not sure how this went unnoticed.

dxil-spirv: Update submodule.

Signed-off-by: Hans-Kristian Arntzen <post@arntzen-software.no>

tests: Disable streamout tests for I/O mismatch for now.

Needs a shader compiler fix. See #1938.

vkd3d: Implement fallback when 2D sparse is not supported.

Relevant for DS sparse on RADV. Convert to a committed resource
and pretend all pages are mapped at all times.
Technically out of spec, but should be good enough to work around games until we have proper support.

Signed-off-by: Hans-Kristian Arntzen <post@arntzen-software.no>

vkd3d: Split shader caches up by exe-name when using explicit directory.

Fixes a usability problem when using explicit VKD3D_SHADER_CACHE_PATH.
For working-directory derived shader cache path, don't replace the name.

Signed-off-by: Hans-Kristian Arntzen <post@arntzen-software.no>

common: Fix questionable implementation of strlcpy/lcat.

strncat doesn't work like you'd expect.
Also gets rid of strncpy since it tends to trip constant compiler
warnings, just replace with memcpy.

Signed-off-by: Hans-Kristian Arntzen <post@arntzen-software.no>

tests: Add test for sparse depth-stencil rendering.

Signed-off-by: Hans-Kristian Arntzen <post@arntzen-software.no>

tests: Refactor out sparse test shaders to headers.

Signed-off-by: Hans-Kristian Arntzen <post@arntzen-software.no>

vkd3d: Don't try to overtake the LL2 sleep cycle.

If the GPU queue is too deep, back off from trying to use latency
fences, and instead rely on low-latency sleeps to clean it up.

Avoids some questionable NV driver behavior where driver will not sleep
when we are also blocking on swapchain backpressure.

Signed-off-by: Hans-Kristian Arntzen <post@arntzen-software.no>

vkd3d: Add more debug information when using latency debug.

Signed-off-by: Hans-Kristian Arntzen <post@arntzen-software.no>

vkd3d: Reset low latency state on DXGI swapchain recreation.

Signed-off-by: Hans-Kristian Arntzen <post@arntzen-software.no>

dxil-spirv: Update submodule.

Signed-off-by: Hans-Kristian Arntzen <post@arntzen-software.no>

meta: Update CHANGELOG.

Signed-off-by: Philip Rebohle <philip.rebohle@tu-dortmund.de>

tests: Test PSO sample count mismatch.

Signed-off-by: Philip Rebohle <philip.rebohle@tu-dortmund.de>

vkd3d: Enable dynamic sample count for multisampled pipelines.

Allows us to work around app bugs where PSO and render target sample
counts do not match.

Signed-off-by: Philip Rebohle <philip.rebohle@tu-dortmund.de>

vkd3d: Enable VK_EXT_extended_dynamic_state3 if supported.

Needed for dynamic rasterization samples.

Signed-off-by: Philip Rebohle <philip.rebohle@tu-dortmund.de>

vkd3d: Remove unused vertex strides from pipeline key.

Signed-off-by: Philip Rebohle <philip.rebohle@tu-dortmund.de>

vkd3d: Remove Cyberpunk 2077 shader quirks

The bug has been fixed game-side.

Signed-off-by: Friedrich Vock <friedrich.vock@gmx.de>

vkd3d: Don't attempt to use rdtsc on ARM64EC

While __x86_64__ is defined when targeting ARM64EC, x86 intrinsics
aren't available.

Signed-off-by: Billy Laws <blaws05@gmail.com>
